                   Preliminary Announcement
                              and
                        Call for Papers

             U.K. Performance Engineering Workshop
                              for
            Computer and Telecommunication Systems

                         to be held at
             Loughborough University of Technology
       Department of Electronic & Electrical Engineering
                   12th and 13th July, 1993

The U.K. Performance Engineering Workshop focuses on the
application of performance and reliability modelling techniques
to the design of efficient and dependable computer and
communication systems. Papers detailing practical and theoretical
aspects of performance engineering will be welcomed.

Papers are encouraged in, but by no means restricted to, the
following areas:-

     o  Analytical modelling techniques
     o  Performance modelling case studies
     o  Reliability analysis and performability
     o  Performance optimization
     o  System measurement
     o  Workload modelling
     o  Simulation techniques and statistical analysis


Submission

Authors are invited to submit three hard copies of extended
abstracts of papers (3-5 double-spaced pages) to the program
chair, by 31st March 1993. The author(s) name and address,
telephone number, and e-mail address (if available) should be
included. Notification of acceptance will be issued by 30th April
1993 and copies of full papers for the Workshop Proceedings must
be received by 5th June 1993.

