                        Further Details

The Location:  Loughborough University is housed on one of the
               largest campuses in the UK, and can be
               conveniently reached from all parts of the
               country -

     By road - Just off the M1 (Junction 23)

     By rail - 90 minutes from London (approx. 10 minutes Taxi
               from Railway Station)

     By air -  East Midlands Airport (approx. 15 minutes - M1)
               Birmingham Airport (approx. 45 minutes - M42/M1)


Accommodation: Choices of accommodation will include - 
               
     Basic -   Student Hall of Residence on campus

     Superior - En-suite facilities (equivalent to 4-star), at
               the University's Burleigh Court Short Course
               Centre, again on campus

     Other -   Alternative accommodation can be arranged to suit
               individual needs - contact Sharon Laing for
               details
 

The Workshop:  In addition to contributed papers the Workshop
               will include -
               
     Invited talks - A Keynote Address by an eminent speaker is
               planned for each day

     Book display - A display of books relating to Performance
               Engineering is planned. Potential exhibitors
               (Publishers/Authors/Editors) should contact the
               program chair

     Demonstration - A practical demonstration of performance
               measurement for a fibre optic based slotted ring
               supporting the Orwell Protocol is being arranged.
               This is believed to be the only existing practical
               implementation of this protocol, and forms part
               of an ATM testbed for British Telecom and SERC
               supported projects

     Proceedings - In addition to the Workshop proceedings, it
               is hoped to publish a selected set of high quality
               papers in book form. Papers for this volume will
               be subjected to further refereeing




